- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the application of speaker recognition for the detection of collaborations in YouTube videos, which involves analyzing multimedia content.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper utilizes face recognition for the detection of collaborators in YouTube videos, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves analyzing spoken language in YouTube videos using speaker recognition, which falls under the domain of computation and language.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves analyzing and detecting collaborations in YouTube videos, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an extension of an existing framework using active speaker detection and speaker recognition, which involves the use of machine learning techniques.
